Project description

google-crc32c

This package wraps the google/crc32chardware-based implementation of the CRC32C hashing algorithm. Multiple wheelsare distributed as well as source. If a wheel is not published for the pythonversion and platform you are using, you will need to compile crc32c using aC toolchain.

Currently Published Wheels

Wheels are currently published for Python 3.7, 3.8, 3.9, 3.10, 3.11 andpypy-3.7 for multiple architectures. For information on building your own,please view BUILDING.md.

Linux

Wheels are published for the following platforms / architectures:

  • manylinux2010 platform, x86_64 and 1686 architectures
  • manylinux2014 platform, aarch64 architecture

Deprecated

  • manylinux1 platform, x86_64 architecture wheels will be built until2021-12-31, when the PyPA group drops support for the manylinux1 image.See: https://github.com/pypa/manylinux/issues/994

Mac OS

Wheels are published for x86_64 and universal2 architectures.

Windows

Wheels are published for win32 and win_amd64 architectures.
